Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
createPipelineNetGroup(25.10)                    createPipelineNetGroup(25.10)

Name
       createPipelineNetGroup  -  Creates  Net  Groups  for Pipeline Flip-Flop
       (PFF) Placement and Reporting

Syntax
       createPipelineNetGroup

       [-help]

       netGroupName

       [-endReserve <reserveDistanceInMicrons>]

       [-endTerm <termList>]

       [-inst <instNameListOrRegularExp>]

       [-net <listOfNetnamesOrRegularExp>]

       [-startReserve <reserveDistanceInMicrons>]

       [-startTerm <termList>]

       Creates Net Groups for Pipeline Flip-Flop (PFF) Placement  and  Report-
       ing.  This  command  can be used for analysis before the flops exist in
       the netlist; or it can be used post flop insertion to  add  a  new  net
       group.

Parameters
       -endReserve <reserveDistanceInMicrons>
              Specifies a distance value from the end points on block boundary
              to  the internal connection inside the block, which is accounted
              for in each stage distance value. The unit is in micron.

       -endTerm <termList>
              Specifies the end points of net groups.

       <netGroupName>
              Specifies the name of the net group.

       -inst <instNameListOrRegularExp>
              Creates net group of all nets connected to the given  instances.
              All  the  instances  must be flip-flops or latches. All the nets
              attached to the D and Q pins are put into the PFF net group.

       -net <listOfNetNamesOrRegularEx><p>
              Creates net group of all given nets.

       -startReserve <reserveDistanceInMicrons>
              Specifies a distance budget  from  internal  connections  inside
              block  to the start point of the PFF net. This value is added to
              the first stage distance when  calculating  equidistant  spacing
              for each stage. The unit is in micron.

       -startTerm <termList>
              Creates net group of all data nets between the given end points.
              The PFF-chain is traced from the startTerm, through D and Q ter-
              minals of PFF(s) until an endTerm is matched.

Example
              * The  following  command  creates a net group named `netGroup1'
                for  Pipeline  Flip-Flop  (PFF)  of  all  data  nets   between
                blockA/DATA_OUT* and blockB/DATA_IN*:

                createPipelineNetGroup  netGroup1  -startTerm blockA/DATA_OUT*
                -endTerm blockB/DATA_IN*

              * The following command creates a net group named netGroup2  for
                all  nets  connected  with  all instance names that begin with
                PIPELINE_INST/in:

                createPipelineNetGroup NetGroup2 -inst PIPELINE_INST/in*

              * The following command creates a net group named netGroup3  for
                all net names that begin with SUM_P4.

                createPipelineNetGroup NetGroup3 -net SUM_P4*

Related Information
